  deck: "An action platformer that follows King Knight's journey to join the Order of no Quarter.",
  description: '<h2>Overview</h2><p>Shovel Knight: King of Cards is an additional campaign developed by <a href="/yacht-club-games/3010-8654/" data-ref-id="3010-8654">Yacht Club Games</a>, that will conclude the Shovel Knight: Treasure Trove series. Players take on the role of Knight King (previously a boss character) as he journeys to ascend to the throne.</p><h2>Gameplay</h2><p>Staying true to the traditional Shovel Knight theme, King of Cards is predominantly an 8-bit 2D side-scrolling platformer. However, unlike previous campaigns, it will also feature a brand new in-game card battling system.</p><h2>Features</h2><p>Shovel Knight: King of Cards will contain the following features:</p><ul><li>4 new worlds.</li><li>Over 30 new courses.</li><li>New attacks and abilities - <em>such as "Bash attack" and "Spinning strike"</em>.</li><li>New weapons and armor.</li><li>Compete in the new card battling mode.</li><li>New Game+ mode.</li><li>Additional "Feats" and "Challenge Stages".</li><li>New bosses to challenge.</li></ul><h2>Soundtrack</h2><p><a href="/yacht-club-games/3010-8654/" data-ref-id="3010-8654">Yacht Club Games</a> have confirmed that long-standing Shovel Knight composer <a href="/jake-kaufman/3040-51915/" data-ref-id="3040-51915">Jake Kaufman</a> will be working on the King of Cards soundtrack.</p>',
