  deck: "Mortal Kombat's eleventh installment involves the time guardian Kronika intending to fix Raiden's mistakes which splintered the timeline.",
  description: "<h2>Overview</h2><figure data-align=\"right\" data-size=\"medium\" data-img-src=\"https://static.giantbomb.com/uploads/original/0/26/3075997-vlcsnap-2019-01-18-10h59m55s083.png\" data-ref-id=\"1300-3075997\" data-ratio=\"0.5625\" data-width=\"1920\" data-embed-type=\"image\" style=\"width: 1920px\"><a class=\"fluid-height\" style=\"padding-bottom:56.3%\" href=\"https://static.giantbomb.com/uploads/original/0/26/3075997-vlcsnap-2019-01-18-10h59m55s083.png\" data-ref-id=\"1300-3075997\"><img alt=\"Fatalities and Brutalities will return in MK11.\" src=\"https://static.giantbomb.com/uploads/scale_medium/0/26/3075997-vlcsnap-2019-01-18-10h59m55s083.jpg\" srcset=\"https://static.giantbomb.com/uploads/original/0/26/3075997-vlcsnap-2019-01-18-10h59m55s083.png 1920w, https://static.giantbomb.com/uploads/scale_super/0/26/3075997-vlcsnap-2019-01-18-10h59m55s083.jpg 960w, https://static.giantbomb.com/uploads/scale_medium/0/26/3075997-vlcsnap-2019-01-18-10h59m55s083.jpg 480w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 480px) 100vw, 480px\" data-width=\"480\"></a><figcaption>Fatalities and Brutalities will return in MK11.</figcaption></figure><p>Mortal Kombat 11 is the third <a href=\"/mortal-kombat/3025-7/\" data-ref-id=\"3025-7\">Mortal Kombat</a> game set in the rebooted universe. The story involves time-travel and timelines, allowing characters to interact with younger versions of themselves. A new boss character, <a href=\"/kronika/3005-39452/\" data-ref-id=\"3005-39452\">Kronika</a>, has control over time itself, allowing her character to be involved in events leading all the way back to the first game in the series.</p><p>As in previous games, players earn and spend meter for various moves and abilities. Unlike previous entries, MK11 has split its meters into offensive and defensive components. Super moves, called \"<a href=\"/xray-damage/3015-8555/\" data-ref-id=\"3015-8555\">X-Rays</a>\" in previous games, have been replaced with \"Fatal Blow\" attacks, which can be triggered when a player is at or below 30% health.</p><p>Characters can be customized cosmetically as well as from a gameplay perspective, with new moves that can be mapped onto a fighter, replacing or enhancing some of their base moves. Different versions of <a href=\"/sub-zero/3005-2/\" data-ref-id=\"3005-2\">Sub-Zero</a>, for example, may have his traditional slide or a standing shoulder charge.</p><p>The game also features consumable augments that can enhance a character's abilities and stats. Other consumables allow players to summon missiles, meteors, or even other characters for assist attacks. These summons appear to be missing from the multiplayer side of the game, but can be used in the Towers of Time, a rotating list of challenges that are pattern after MKX's Living Towers or <a href=\"/injustice-2/3030-54144/\" data-ref-id=\"3030-54144\">Injustice 2</a>'s Multiverse. Summons are activated by flicking the right analog stick in a specific direction.</p><h2>Roster</h2><figure data-align=\"right\" data-size=\"medium\" data-img-src=\"https://static.giantbomb.com/uploads/scale_super/0/1992/3078498-sha256_9992290016b263e1b463b3766b9dfd76be85875c34d43f0de1edcb60067d24d4.jpeg\" data-ref-id=\"1300-3078498\" data-ratio=\"0.5625\" data-width=\"1920\" data-embed-type=\"image\" style=\"width: 1920px\"><a class=\"fluid-height\" style=\"padding-bottom:56.3%\" href=\"https://static.giantbomb.com/uploads/scale_super/0/1992/3078498-sha256_9992290016b263e1b463b3766b9dfd76be85875c34d43f0de1edcb60067d24d4.jpeg\" data-ref-id=\"1300-3078498\"><img alt=\"Skarlet has been heavily redesigned since her debut in Mortal Kombat (2011).\" src=\"https://static.giantbomb.com/uploads/scale_medium/0/1992/3078498-sha256_9992290016b263e1b463b3766b9dfd76be85875c34d43f0de1edcb60067d24d4.jpeg\" srcset=\"https://static.giantbomb.com/uploads/original/0/1992/3078498-sha256_9992290016b263e1b463b3766b9dfd76be85875c34d43f0de1edcb60067d24d4.jpeg 1920w, https://static.giantbomb.com/uploads/scale_super/0/1992/3078498-sha256_9992290016b263e1b463b3766b9dfd76be85875c34d43f0de1edcb60067d24d4.jpeg 960w, https://static.giantbomb.com/uploads/scale_medium/0/1992/3078498-sha256_9992290016b263e1b463b3766b9dfd76be85875c34d43f0de1edcb60067d24d4.jpeg 480w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 480px) 100vw, 480px\" data-width=\"480\"></a><figcaption>Skarlet has been heavily redesigned since her debut in Mortal Kombat (2011).</figcaption></figure><p>While many characters may appear in Mortal Kombat 11's story mode, these are ones who are playable on the <a href=\"/character-select-screen/3015-2125/\" data-ref-id=\"3015-2125\">character select screen</a>.</p><ul><li><a href=\"/baraka/3005-64/\" data-ref-id=\"3005-64\">Baraka</a></li><li><a href=\"/cassie-cage/3005-29593/\" data-ref-id=\"3005-29593\">Cassie Cage</a></li><li><a href=\"/d-vorah/3005-29591/\" data-ref-id=\"3005-29591\">D’Vorah</a></li><li><a href=\"/erron-black/3005-31428/\" data-ref-id=\"3005-31428\">Erron Black</a></li><li><a href=\"/geras/3005-39448/\" data-ref-id=\"3005-39448\">Geras</a></li><li><a href=\"/jacqueline-briggs/3005-31423/\" data-ref-id=\"3005-31423\">Jacqui Briggs</a></li><li><a href=\"/jade/3005-386/\" data-ref-id=\"3005-386\">Jade</a></li><li><a href=\"/jax/3005-235/\" data-ref-id=\"3005-235\">Jax</a></li><li><a href=\"/johnny-cage/3005-224/\" data-ref-id=\"3005-224\">Johnny Cage</a></li><li><a href=\"/kabal/3005-218/\" data-ref-id=\"3005-218\">Kabal</a></li><li><a href=\"/kano/3005-216/\" data-ref-id=\"3005-216\">Kano</a></li><li><a href=\"/kotal-kahn/3005-29596/\" data-ref-id=\"3005-29596\">Kotal Kahn</a></li><li><a href=\"/kung-lao/3005-392/\" data-ref-id=\"3005-392\">Kung Lao</a></li><li><a href=\"/liu-kang/3005-188/\" data-ref-id=\"3005-188\">Liu Kang</a></li><li><a href=\"/noob-saibot/3005-152/\" data-ref-id=\"3005-152\">Noob Saibot</a></li><li><a href=\"/raiden/3005-125/\" data-ref-id=\"3005-125\">Raiden</a></li><li><a href=\"/scorpion/3005-1/\" data-ref-id=\"3005-1\">Scorpion</a></li><li><a href=\"/shang-tsung/3005-92/\" data-ref-id=\"3005-92\">Shang Tsung</a> (DLC)</li><li><a href=\"/shao-kahn/3005-91/\" data-ref-id=\"3005-91\">Shao Kahn</a> (DLC)</li><li><a href=\"/sonya-blade/3005-70/\" data-ref-id=\"3005-70\">Sonya Blade</a></li><li><a href=\"/sub-zero/3005-2/\" data-ref-id=\"3005-2\">Sub-Zero</a></li></ul><p> </p>",
